                     <title xml:lang="en">Latin charter</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Latin grant by Johanna de Bramtona, widow of Ralph de Vermels, with the consent of her son Philip in  to Newhouse Abbey, of the village of Eskholme in Brampton [Lincolnshire]. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Attached to the Latin grant is two Latin quitclaims, each with a Hebrew docket: Harley ch 43 A 66 B and Harley ch 43 A 66 C.</p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                  
                  
                  
